article.headline: Illinois St. 65, Evansville 61
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Osiris Eldridge scored 14 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Illinois State mustered a 65-61 comeback win over Evansville on Tuesday night. The Redbirds (12-11, 4-8 Missouri Valley) trailed 32-29 at halftime and by as many as 10 with 14:22 left in the game. They tied it up 57-57 when Eldridge hit a 3-pointer with 1:54 remaining. Eldridge scored six more points down the stretch, including two free throws with 3 seconds left, to seal the victory. Jason Holsinger went 6-of-10 from 3-point range while scoring 24 points, including 19 in the first half, to lead the Purple Aces (12-11, 5-7). Matt Webster chipped in 18 points for Evansville. Anthony Slack scored 14 points and pulled down nine rebounds in a reserve role for Illinois State and the Redbirds' bench outscored the Purple Aces' reserves 24-6. Boo Richardson chipped in 11 points and five assists for Illinois State, which outrebounded the Purple Aces 34-24 and outscored them 26-18 in the paint.
